# Report development — investigation mode

Before changing reports, read `docs/REPORT_DEVELOPMENT.md`.

## Rule (mandatory)

When **investigation mode is ON**, all report date filters must be capped to the **current fiscal year** (default Jul 1 – Jun 30, via `InvestigationMode`). Applies to **every role** including superadmin. Non-report features are unchanged.

## Implementation

In `ReportController`, always use:

- `$this->resolveReportDates($from, $to, $defaultFrom, $defaultTo)` for ranges
- `$this->resolveAsOfDate($asOf, $default)` for as-of dates
- `$this->attachReportPeriodMeta($data, $range)` for view notice

Never read raw `from_date` / `to_date` from request without clamping.

Other controllers: call `InvestigationMode::clampReportDates()` / `clampAsOfDate()` — do not duplicate fiscal logic.

Report models: accept pre-clamped dates from controller only.

## Do not

- Add read-only POST guards or branch scoping for investigation
- Bypass date clamping in export/AJAX endpoints
- Implement fiscal-year math outside `core/InvestigationMode.php`
